MathMetaData

Information about the Math Channels.

Variables
id
uint8 id

The identifier of the algorithm used.

sourceChannel
uint8 sourceChannel

The zero-indexed channel used to run the math calculation.

startOfTrigger
bool startOfTrigger

Whether the current data point is the start of a new trigger.  This will be true for a single data point, in which case all of this DatalogSessionInfo will have been updated with new information.  When moved to the next datapoint, startOfTrigger will be reset to false.

triggerType
WirelessTypes::TriggerType triggerType

The WirelessTypes::TriggerType of the session.

numSweeps
uint32 numSweeps

The total number of sweeps that are in the session.

sweepSize
uint16 sweepSize

The size (number of bytes) of the sweeps in the session.

sessionIndex
uint16 sessionIndex

The datalogging session index. This starts at 1 for the first session, and gets incremented for each additional session.

activeChannels
ChannelMask activeChannels

The ChannelMask for the session.

sampleRate
SampleRate sampleRate

The SampleRate for the session.

timeBetweenSweeps
uint64 timeBetweenSweeps

The number of nanoseconds between each sweep, determined by the sample rate.

dataType
WirelessTypes::DataType dataType

The WirelessTypes::DataType of the session.

valueType
ValueType valueType

The ValueType of the session.

userString
std::string userString

The user entered string of the session (if any).

timestamp
uint64 timestamp

The starting timestamp for the session, in nanoseconds.

calsApplied;

Whether the cal coefficients are applied to the data or not.

calCoefficients
ChannelCalMap calCoefficients

A map of WirelessChannel::ChannelId to CalCoefficients.
